snippet.textDisplay:
Humans all over the globe are now getting a small taste of what they have inflicted on other beings on this earth for centuries, even millennia. 

- Social isolation from our family members. That's what cows in American breeding farms feel when we take away their calves. 
- The trauma of losing our loved ones. That's what elephants in Africa feel when we massacre them. 
- Boredom and anxiety. That's what pandas feel who are locked up for decades in small cages in Chinese zoos. 
- Fear about our fate. That's what dogs trapped in cages feel before being boiled alive in South Korea.
- Worry about our health.

And we still have it good! We can watch movies, order the food we like, read books, drink wine, facetime our friends, and likely get healthcare when we get ill. Our suffering in quarantine is comfortable.

Every pandemic originated in the abuse and consumption of animals. MERS, SARS, swine flu, bird flu, Jacob Creuzfeld, ... see a pattern here? No pandemic was ever caused by eating plants. If we make the planet suffer, it will make us suffer. If we continue slaughtering 60 billion animals per year, we are just begging for this virus to mutate and become even deadlier next time. Is this the world we want to give our children?

Instead of complaining about being bored, be grateful for every day you're alive and healthy. And use this time to self-reflect: How did this global pandemic come about? Is it a random event, or are we humans collectively responsible? What was your individual role in this tragedy?
